nodes.bodyText:
Every time I see this in FXML files I cringe a bit 😞
I've recently used CSS to get rid of some of this stuff and hide it in styles.css:
https://github.com/Esri/arcgis-runtime-samples-java/pull/498/files
Perhaps we can make that a regular thing with new samples?
The trick is to add styleClass="stack-pane" to the StackPane, and then you can target individual FXML elements with rules, e.g. for a VBox:
.stack-pane VBox {
  -fx-text-fill: white;
    -fx-background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    -fx-padding: 10;
    -fx-max-width: 200;
    -fx-max-height: 120;
    -fx-spacing: 10;
}

It'll also allow you to hide away a lot of the max width etc. definitions.

